main event: A civilian observed an unidentified flying object in Austin, Texas, on August 24, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 25 seconds and appeared to move in a northerly direction., The sighting was consistent with satellite observation according to the conclusion in the report., The weather conditions were clear at night when the object was observed., The witness described the object as a pale, silver, disc-shaped object about the size of a Volkswagen bug., The object exhibited changing colors from white to amber to green while hovering.
witness description: A civilian male, age 45, who reported seeing the object while in a residential section of the city.
